cape its grasp. Now, a new middle ground is emerging between religious and secular Jews who want to engage with their heritage—without being restricted by it or losing it completely. In this incisive book, acclaimed author Micah Goodman explores Israeli Judaism and the conflict between religion and secularism, one of the major causes of political polarization throughout the world. Revisiting traditional religious sources and seminal works of secularism, he reveals that each contains an openness to learn from the other’s messages. Goodman challenges both orthodoxies, proposing a new approach to bridge the divide between religion and secularism and pave a path toward healing a society torn asunder by extremism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh1 aLevy, Eylon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069231040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300255997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300255997.jpg  a978-3-11-069231-0  YUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070477-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020